═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  certs/ — Embedded Dev Certificate (Compile-Time)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  This directory holds the DEVELOPMENT fallback certificate that
  gets compiled directly into the unikernel binary.

  Files:
    dev-cert.pem   ← Self-signed EC P-256 cert (10-year validity)
    dev-key.pem    ← Corresponding private key

  How it works:
    src/tls.rs uses include_str!("../certs/dev-cert.pem") to bake
    these into the binary at compile time. If no production certs
    are found at /data/tls/ on boot, this fallback is used.

  This is NOT where production certificates go.
  For production certs → see data/tls/README

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
